    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This unit maintains factory-spec boost pressures and exhibits excellent compression across all rotor faces. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, delivering power to the rear wheels with zero drivetrain lash. The suspension geometry remains true, utilizing the original aluminum double-wishbone setup for telepathic handling. With a flawless exterior and an interior devoid of the typical plastics degradation, this specimen represents the pinnacle of 90s JDM performance engineering. Mechanically sorted and aesthetically preserved.",
